Since its inception in 1985, Microsoft Windows has evolved into one of the most widely used operating systems for both personal and enterprise environments.
From Windows 1.0 to the robust capabilities of Windows 10 and Windows Server 2019, it has become a critical platform in modern IT operations and cybersecurity.
This section of my portfolio explores the intersection of System Administration and Cybersecurity (CyberOps) on Windows-based systems.
It focuses on how Windows operates under the hood and highlights practical techniques and tools
used to secure, monitor,
and respond to threats on Windows endpoints and servers.
